  "body": "Hey, it's Rick!\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nIf you're feeling exhausted from trying to get AI to just \"work\"\r\nfor you and your business, you're not alone.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nSome are calling it \"AI fatigue,\" and it's real.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nBut after watching hundreds of people go through it first-hand,\r\nincluding myself, I can tell you it's almost never about the AI.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nLet's dive in...\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nToday’s Playbook:\r\n-----------------\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n* Why AI fatigue is real, and why it’s not the AI’s fault\r\n* Members building CRMs, new homepages with Claude Design, and\r\ncontent machines (Community Wins)\r\n* The one question that flips your entire AI dynamic (Your\r\n10-Minute Play)\r\n* A trip to New Hampshire, bad coffee, and a 7-year-old who\r\ntravels better than most adults (Meanwhile)\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n☕☕☕\r\n​\r\n\r\nWhat I'm Seeing...\r\n------------------\r\n\r\n​\r\nLast week, one of my AI Playbook members showed up to our Q&A\r\ncall exhausted.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nShe’s in the middle of a big transition in her business and was\r\ntrying to map out the next six weeks with Claude's help.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nTo do that, she wanted a 7-day time-block plan, something she\r\ncould look at each week and know exactly what she was working on\r\nand when.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nShe’d spent hours, not 20 minutes, hours, inside Claude Code\r\ntrying to build it.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nShe’s smart. She knows how to use AI, yet she still walked away\r\ndrained.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nWhen I asked her what happened, she said that she “felt like she\r\nwas doing all the thinking for Claude.”\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nAnd because she’s making so many changes in her business, and\r\nhaving Claude help her, she felt like she was carrying a big\r\ncognitive load.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nShe was right.\r\n​\r\n\r\nHere’s what was actually going on…\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nShe wanted Claude to take her calendar, her priorities, and her\r\nmental and time constraints, and output a visual schedule she\r\ncould actually work from each week.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nOnce she was able to clearly articulate that, Claude went ahead\r\nand did it for her\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nThe output was exactly what she wanted.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nBut here was the problem…\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nEvery time she wanted to regenerate it, she had to re-explain\r\neverything from scratch: her schedule, her workload, her current\r\npriorities, her constraints.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nClaude had no memory of any of it.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nSo the tool that was supposed to save her time was actually\r\ncreating more work for her.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nClaude didn’t have any background on how she works.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nNo context on her business model, her audience, her offers, her\r\nvoice, or her priorities.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nEvery session started at zero (even with Claude’s Memory\r\nfeature).\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nAnd because Claude didn’t have that foundation, it kept bouncing\r\nideas back to her.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nEvery output required a judgment call. Every response kicked a\r\ndecision back to her.\r\n\r\nShe wasn’t experiencing AI fatigue.\r\n\r\nShe was experiencing decision fatigue caused by missing\r\ninfrastructure, meaning a simple context file(s) that tells\r\nClaude who you are, how you work, and what matters most in your\r\nbusiness.\r\n\r\nThe AI wasn’t the problem.\r\n\r\nThe missing context files were.\r\n\r\nThis is the most common bottleneck I see right now.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nPeople think they’re bad at prompting, or that AI isn’t quite\r\ngood enough yet, or that they just need to try harder.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nBut the real issue is that they haven’t given Claude what it\r\nneeds to actually be useful.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nWhen Claude knows your business (your offers, your audience, your\r\ncommunication style, your priorities, your preferences), it stops\r\nbouncing decisions back to you.\r\nThe cognitive load shifts off your plate because Claude can then\r\njust do the work you want it to do.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nThat’s when AI stops being exhausting and starts feeling like\r\nleverage.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n☕☕☕\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nYour 10-Minute Play:\r\n--------------------\r\n\r\n​\r\nMost people go to AI with a task: “Write this. Draft that. Build\r\nthis for me.”\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nAll well and good but the AI needs context about you if it’s\r\ngoing to be helpful.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nSo if you haven’t already done this, before you ask Claude to do\r\nanything, ask it what it needs from you.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nOpen a new chat and paste this:\r\n\r\nI want to use you as a thinking partner and executor\r\nfor my business. Before we start, I need you to ask me the\r\nquestions that would make you most useful to me.\r\n\r\nAsk about my business model, my audience, my offers, my\r\ncurrent priorities, my communication style, and anything else\r\nyou'd need to give me high-quality, personalized output — not\r\ngeneric advice.\r\n\r\nAsk me one question at a time. Once you have enough,\r\nsummarize what you know about me and how you'll apply it.\r\n\r\n+ ◴\r\n\r\n↑\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nThis single conversation will help Claude understand your\r\nspecific preferences, experience and business and thus make it\r\nway more useful to you.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nSave the summary Claude gives you at the end.\r\n​\r\n\r\n* If you're using regular Claude chat, take that summary and\r\npaste it into the \"What personal preferences should Claude\r\nconsider in responses?\" section in Claude Settings\r\n​\r\nFrom that point on, Claude will have that context in every\r\nconversation automatically.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nIf you're using Claude Code, this same output becomes the basis\r\nfor something even more powerful but outside the scope of this\r\nnewsletter.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nI cover that from start to finish in my brand new Claude Code\r\ntraining inside my community (\r\nhttps://13a5ec89.click.convertkit-mail4.com/wvug77o5n8hghk60lroa7hnd6lx90ame3xrwmkegvzed83qdrdlo87lz0eo963xdz6pevm3nn9gzq6634eqw8lxmwk2w5l6z3lkp43pvvg84ld6p3p56p67z84rbw063/dphehmuenegm2qtl/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2tvb2wuY29tL2FpLXBsYXlib29rL2Fib3V0\r\n).\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n☕☕☕\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nCommunity Wins\r\n--------------\r\n\r\nSometimes the best ideas come from seeing what others are doing.\r\nHere are some wins from our AI Playbook members (\r\nhttps://13a5ec89.click.convertkit-mail4.com/wvug77o5n8hghk60lroa7hnd6lx90ame3xrwmkegvzed83qdrdlo87lz0eo963xdz6pevm3nn9gzq6634eqw8lxmwk2w5l6z3lkp43pvvg84ld6p3p56p67z84rbw063/kkh5g43di2unvnq3o8hk/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2tvb2wuY29tL2FpLXBsYXlib29rL2Fib3V0\r\n) over the last week:\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n* Gilbert transformed his social media content discovery process\r\nusing AI, turning hours of manual scrolling into a streamlined\r\nsystem that identifies clips worth remixing, reaction content,\r\nand actionable ideas in minutes.\r\n​\r\n* Laura built and redesigned her own CRM in one afternoon using\r\nClaude Design, turning what used to be a year-long search for the\r\nright visual system into a custom solution that perfectly matches\r\nher workflow as a solo realtor.\r\n​\r\n* Joni set up her design system in Claude Design and was\r\nsurprised when it automatically generated a website mockup,\r\nturning her old homepage into a fresh design that's ready to\r\nimplement.\r\n​\r\n* Silke created a custom rule in her AI system that automatically\r\nchecks everything her team produces, backing up every idea with\r\nstructured feedback and eliminating manual oversight entirely.\r\n​\r\n* Shelly started using AI for document review and revision,\r\nstreamlining her content creation process across social channels\r\nwhile tackling her brand book next.\r\n​\r\n* Alan dove into Claude Code this week, transforming his\r\ndevelopment workflow even with a packed schedule and getting\r\naccess to capabilities he didn't want to wait to explore.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n☕☕☕\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nMeanwhile...\r\n------------\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n* Spent most of last week in New Hampshire with my daughter\r\nvisiting my mom, who isn’t doing well. Really nice trip despite\r\nthe circumstances. I don’t miss the East Coast one bit though.\r\n​\r\n* Tried so many coffee spots near where we were and couldn’t find\r\nanything! even half decent. So glad to be back home with the good\r\nstuff.\r\n​\r\n* My daughter is 7 and she is an unbelievable traveler. Flights,\r\ndelays, schedule changes, new environment. She just rolls with\r\nall of it. I don’t know where she gets it but I’m not questioning\r\nit.\r\n\r\nYou Shouldn't Have to Explain Your Business to AI Every Single\r\nTime\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nYou've been doing all the thinking for Claude.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nRe-explaining who you are, what you sell, who you serve. Every.\r\nSingle. Session.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nThat's the problem Your Zone of Genius app solves.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nOpen it Monday morning and your CMO has the week's content\r\nmapped. Your sales copywriter has three email drafts ready for\r\nreview.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nYour executive assistant already cleared the noise from your\r\ninbox.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nThat's what AI Playbook members are doing right now inside the\r\nYour Zone of Genius app (\r\nhttps://13a5ec89.click.convertkit-mail4.com/wvug77o5n8hghk60lroa7hnd6lx90ame3xrwmkegvzed83qdrdlo87lz0eo963xdz6pevm3nn9gzq6634eqw8lxmwk2w5l6z3lkp43pvvg84ld6p3p56p67z84rbw063/dphehmuenegm2qtl/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2tvb2wuY29tL2FpLXBsYXlib29rL2Fib3V0\r\n).\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nMost AI training teaches you how to prompt ChatGPT or make a GPT.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nThat's so 2024.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nYour Zone of Genius app gives you access to an entire team that's\r\ncustomized to your business, your voice, your style, your\r\naudience while trained with my frameworks, experience and IP.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nYour marketing team: Content Creator & Strategist, Email\r\nMarketing Manager, Sales Copywriter, Conversion Rate Optimization\r\nSpecialist\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nYour strategy team: Chief Marketing Officer, CEO, Offer\r\nStrategist, Revenue Optimization Specialist\r\n​\r\n​PickRicksBrain: my AI coaching chatbot for on-demand business\r\nstrategy (I built this in early 2023 and have been refining it\r\nsince).\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nYour operations: Executive Assistant\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nNew roles added every week.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nPrefer to build your own?\r\n\r\nIf you're the type who wants to roll up your sleeves and build\r\ncustom AI solutions and agents for your specific business, the\r\napp is your foundation.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nYou get my frameworks, my IP, and the training to build anything\r\nyou need, from a custom sales agent to a workflow no one's\r\nthought of yet.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nUse the team I've built for you. Build your own. Or both.\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n\"The app streamlines 95% of my work into one place so I don't\r\nhave to keep reinventing the wheel.\" -- Laura S., AI Playbook\r\nmember\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n\"Started using it and kicked out some of the best email series.\r\nThis just feels so much more organized and complete.\" -- Stefanie\r\nA., AI Playbook member\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n\"Your zone of genius app helped me with my priority this week —\r\nto develop a marketing strategy aimed to achieve my goals and a\r\n90 day plan to execute! I’m loving the app so far!\" -- Alyssa B.,\r\nAI Playbook member\r\n​\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n-->Start Your 7-Day Free Trial Today (\r\nhttps://13a5ec89.click.convertkit-mail4.com/wvug77o5n8hghk60lroa7hnd6lx90ame3xrwmkegvzed83qdrdlo87lz0eo963xdz6pevm3nn9gzq6634eqw8lxmwk2w5l6z3lkp43pvvg84ld6p3p56p67z84rbw063/owheqr68fwuwdwv704uq/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2tvb2wuY29tL2FpLXBsYXlib29rL2Fib3V0\r\n)\r\nStart Your 7-Day Free Trial Today (\r\nhttps://www.skool.com/ai-playbook/about )​\r\n​(immediate full access to the app, the community, and all\r\ntrainings)\r\n\r\n​\r\n​\r\n\r\n\"I’ve used it today it is totally awesome @Rick Mulready i picked\r\nyour brain and felt like I was actually talking to you!\" -- Roma\r\nW., AI Playbook member\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n(\r\nhttps://13a